@{B}1. Rules :
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯ @{UB}
The black box is an 8x8 grid in which several atoms are hidden.
Your job is to find the atoms. You have at your disposal a ray
projector. You can use this to send rays into the box.

A ray may meet with one of three fates. It may hit an atom and
be absorbed, it may be diverted and come out somewhere else or
it may be reflected and come out where it went in.

Rules governing the fate of rays:

@{B}1.@{UB} A ray that hits an atom head on is absorbed and
   never comes back out.
@{B}2.@{UB} A ray that hits an atom to one side is diverted
   90° to that side
@{B}3.@{UB} A ray that passes between two atoms one  square
   apart is reflected, its direction  is  reversed 
   and it retraces its path.
@{B}4.@{UB} A ray that enters alongside an atom is reflected
@{B}5.@{UB} At all other times a ray follows a straight path
@{B}6.@{UB} A ray may bounce off more than one atom

@{B}2. Gameplay :
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯ @{UB}
To send in a ray use the mouse to select the entry point  for
the ray. It will start out travelling vertically or  horizon-
tally depending on which side it enters.

You will be told wether the ray is absorbed by an atom (Entry
point will be marked with a capital A), is  reflected ( Entry
point will be marked with a capital B) or comes out.
If it comes out, you will be told where ( Entrance  and  Exit
will be marked with the same letter).

Put 4 atoms on the grid by selecting grid positions with  the 
mouse. Selecting 'Solve' will compare the actual position  of
the atoms with the user-suggested positions.If the user fails
to locate all atoms penalty-points will be added to his score.

Select the time-limit option to increase the level  of  diff-
iculty. 

